@startuml body_lock_to_ambient_change_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Body Lock To Ambient Change Signal Flow\n(Input_Console -> Router -> BCM -> IVI)

actor "Driver\n(Input Console)" as Driver #F4F7FB
participant "Input_Console\nVehicle > Body + Signals" as Panel #E8F0FE
participant "INPUT_CONSOLE_ROUTER\nbutton pulse normalizer" as Router #FFF4CC
participant "BCM\nbody / comfort owner" as BCM #E8F7E8
participant "IVI\nambient render consumer" as IVI #E8F0FE

== Manual Cabin Access Commands ==

Driver -> Panel : Click UNLOCK / LOCK\nselect ambient mode
activate Panel
Panel -> Panel : Write Cmd::doorUnlock / Cmd::doorLock\nand Cmd::ambientModeCmd
note right of Panel
Input seams
- Cmd::doorUnlock / doorLock / doorLockHold
- Cmd::ambientModeCmd
end note
deactivate Panel

== Router Normalization ==

activate Router
Panel -> Router : Cmd::* button pulses
Router -> Router : doorUnlock -> Cmd::doorLockCmd = 1
Router -> Router : doorLock -> Cmd::doorLockCmd = 2
Router -> Router : clear one-shot pulse vars
note right of Router
Router keeps the panel UI simple
while BCM consumes normalized
doorLockCmd and ambientModeCmd.
end note
deactivate Router

== BCM Ownership ==

activate BCM
Router -> BCM : Cmd::doorLockCmd\nCmd::ambientModeCmd
BCM -> BCM : manualMode = (Test::scenarioActiveId == 0)
BCM -> BCM : ambientMode = Cmd::ambientModeCmd\nwhen manualMode
BCM -> BCM : deriveAmbientColorFromMode()
BCM -> BCM : deriveAmbientPatternFromMode()
BCM -> BCM : compute doorLockState / doorOpenWarn
note right of BCM
Representative BCM outputs
- Body::ambientMode / ambientColor / ambientPattern
- frmAmbientControlMsg
- frmInteriorLightMsg
- frmDoorStateMsg
- frmBodyComfortStateMsg
end note
BCM -> IVI : Body::ambientMode / ambientColor / ambientPattern
deactivate BCM

== Visible Cabin Outcome ==

activate IVI
IVI -> IVI : renderMode / renderColor /\nrenderPattern from Body::ambient*
IVI -> Panel : UiRender / Infotainment mirrors
note right of IVI
Ambient rendering follows
BCM-owned body state, while
door lock remains part of the
same cabin-access interaction zone.
end note
deactivate IVI

Driver <- Panel : Lock state / ambient scene\nappear as one body-access context

note over Driver, IVI
Representative runtime chain
1. Input_Console emits door and ambient commands
2. Router normalizes lock pulses into doorLockCmd
3. BCM owns both door-state and ambient-state publication
4. IVI consumes ambient outputs for cabin rendering
end note

@enduml
